{
  "name": "S7-04 AI Agent - Fallback LLM",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Lesson 4: AI Agent Fallback Model\n\n### What you'll learn\n- AI Agents can have multiple LLMs attached\n- If the primary fails (rate limit, outage, key issue), the fallback takes over automatically\n- This applies to AI nodes too — error handling isn't just for HTTP\n\n### Try it\n1. Open the AI Agent → enable 'Needs Fallback Model'\n2. The first LLM input is primary, the second is fallback\n3. Send a chat message → answer comes from primary\n4. Disable your OpenAI credential temporarily → fallback (Gemini) answers instead\n\n### Cost vs reliability\nA fallback model adds resilience but also adds cost when triggered.\nUse a CHEAPER model as fallback when possible (e.g. Gemini Flash).",
        "height": 380,
        "width": 760,
        "color": 7
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-400, -80],
